Monarchs under the aegis of the Association of Christian Traditional Rulers of Nigeria have met with the leadership of the Miyetti Allah Cattle Breeders Association to find a lasting solution to herders/farmers’ conflict. The Chairman and the Secretary of the Association of Christian Traditional Rulers of Nigeria, Eze Nkeli Kelly and King Dodo II, the group in Awka, Anambra State, explained that the parley was fruitful and encouraging. A statement issued to that effect partly read: “The association in collaboration with the Miyetti Allah Cattle Breeders Association of Nigeria is meeting to find a lasting solution to end the herders/farmers’ clashes all over the country. “We also advised all monarchs to educate youths in their areas and other subjects to be law-abiding and shun any form of violence.”